    ("AP_HC","Indian_Polity","The writ of 'Mandamus' means:","We command","To have the body","By what authority","To be certified","A","Easy","Mandamus means 'we command'. It is issued to a public official, body, or lower court directing them to perform a public or statutory duty they have refused to perform."),
